44/* Forward declarations of the private auto-generated matchers.
45 They expect valueized operands in canonical order and do not
46 perform simplification of all-constant operands. */
47static bool gimple_simplify (code_helper *, tree *,
48 gimple_seq *, tree (*)(tree),
49 code_helper, tree, tree);
50static bool gimple_simplify (code_helper *, tree *,
51 gimple_seq *, tree (*)(tree),
52 code_helper, tree, tree, tree);
53static bool gimple_simplify (code_helper *, tree *,
54 gimple_seq *, tree (*)(tree),
55 code_helper, tree, tree, tree, tree);

58/* Return whether T is a constant that we'll dispatch to fold to
59 evaluate fully constant expressions. */
60
61static inline bool
62constant_for_folding (tree t)
63{
64 return (CONSTANT_CLASS_P (t)
65 /* The following is only interesting to string builtins. */
66 || (TREE_CODE (t) == ADDR_EXPR
67 && TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (t, 0)) == STRING_CST));
68}

71/* Helper that matches and simplifies the toplevel result from
72 a gimple_simplify run (where we don't want to build
73 a stmt in case it's used in in-place folding). Replaces
74 *RES_CODE and *RES_OPS with a simplified and/or canonicalized
75 result and returns whether any change was made. */
76
77bool
78gimple_resimplify1 (gimple_seq *seq,
79 code_helper *res_code, tree type, tree *res_ops,
80 tree (*valueize)(tree))
81{
82 if (constant_for_folding (res_ops[0]))
83 {
84 tree tem = NULL_TREE;
85 if (res_code->is_tree_code ())
86 tem = const_unop (*res_code, type, res_ops[0]);
87 else
88 tem = fold_const_call (combined_fn (*res_code), type, res_ops[0]);
89 if (tem != NULL_TREE
90 && CONSTANT_CLASS_P (tem))
91 {
92 if (TREE_OVERFLOW_P (tem))
93 tem = drop_tree_overflow (tem);
94 res_ops[0] = tem;
95 res_ops[1] = NULL_TREE;
96 res_ops[2] = NULL_TREE;
97 *res_code = TREE_CODE (res_ops[0]);
98 return true;
99 }
100 }
101
102 /* Limit recursion, there are cases like PR80887 and others, for
103 example when value-numbering presents us with unfolded expressions
104 that we are really not prepared to handle without eventual
105 oscillation like ((_50 + 0) + 8) where _50 gets mapped to _50
106 itself as available expression. */
107 static unsigned depth;
108 if (depth > 10)
109 {
110 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
111 fprintf (dump_file, "Aborting expression simplification due to "
112 "deep recursion\n");
113 return false;
114 }
115
116 ++depth;
117 code_helper res_code2;
118 tree res_ops2[3] = {};
119 if (gimple_simplify (&res_code2, res_ops2, seq, valueize,
120 *res_code, type, res_ops[0]))
121 {
122 --depth;
123 *res_code = res_code2;
124 res_ops[0] = res_ops2[0];
125 res_ops[1] = res_ops2[1];
126 res_ops[2] = res_ops2[2];
127 return true;
128 }
129 --depth;
130
131 return false;
132}
133
134/* Helper that matches and simplifies the toplevel result from
135 a gimple_simplify run (where we don't want to build
136 a stmt in case it's used in in-place folding). Replaces
137 *RES_CODE and *RES_OPS with a simplified and/or canonicalized
138 result and returns whether any change was made. */
139
140bool
141gimple_resimplify2 (gimple_seq *seq,
142 code_helper *res_code, tree type, tree *res_ops,
143 tree (*valueize)(tree))
144{
145 if (constant_for_folding (res_ops[0]) && constant_for_folding (res_ops[1]))
146 {
147 tree tem = NULL_TREE;
148 if (res_code->is_tree_code ())
149 tem = const_binop (*res_code, type, res_ops[0], res_ops[1]);
150 else
151 tem = fold_const_call (combined_fn (*res_code), type,
152 res_ops[0], res_ops[1]);
153 if (tem != NULL_TREE
154 && CONSTANT_CLASS_P (tem))
155 {
156 if (TREE_OVERFLOW_P (tem))
157 tem = drop_tree_overflow (tem);
158 res_ops[0] = tem;
159 res_ops[1] = NULL_TREE;
160 res_ops[2] = NULL_TREE;
161 *res_code = TREE_CODE (res_ops[0]);
162 return true;
163 }
164 }
165
166 /* Canonicalize operand order. */
167 bool canonicalized = false;
168 if (res_code->is_tree_code ()
169 && (TREE_CODE_CLASS ((enum tree_code) *res_code) == tcc_comparison
170 || commutative_tree_code (*res_code))
171 && tree_swap_operands_p (res_ops[0], res_ops[1]))
172 {
173 std::swap (res_ops[0], res_ops[1]);
174 if (TREE_CODE_CLASS ((enum tree_code) *res_code) == tcc_comparison)
175 *res_code = swap_tree_comparison (*res_code);
176 canonicalized = true;
177 }
178
179 /* Limit recursion, see gimple_resimplify1. */
180 static unsigned depth;
181 if (depth > 10)
182 {
183 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
184 fprintf (dump_file, "Aborting expression simplification due to "
185 "deep recursion\n");
186 return false;
187 }
188
189 ++depth;
190 code_helper res_code2;
191 tree res_ops2[3] = {};
192 if (gimple_simplify (&res_code2, res_ops2, seq, valueize,
193 *res_code, type, res_ops[0], res_ops[1]))
194 {
195 --depth;
196 *res_code = res_code2;
197 res_ops[0] = res_ops2[0];
198 res_ops[1] = res_ops2[1];
199 res_ops[2] = res_ops2[2];
200 return true;
201 }
202 --depth;
203
204 return canonicalized;
205}
206
207/* Helper that matches and simplifies the toplevel result from
208 a gimple_simplify run (where we don't want to build
209 a stmt in case it's used in in-place folding). Replaces
210 *RES_CODE and *RES_OPS with a simplified and/or canonicalized
211 result and returns whether any change was made. */
212
213bool
214gimple_resimplify3 (gimple_seq *seq,
215 code_helper *res_code, tree type, tree *res_ops,
216 tree (*valueize)(tree))
217{
218 if (constant_for_folding (res_ops[0]) && constant_for_folding (res_ops[1])
219 && constant_for_folding (res_ops[2]))
220 {
221 tree tem = NULL_TREE;
222 if (res_code->is_tree_code ())
223 tem = fold_ternary/*_to_constant*/ (*res_code, type, res_ops[0],
224 res_ops[1], res_ops[2]);
225 else
226 tem = fold_const_call (combined_fn (*res_code), type,
227 res_ops[0], res_ops[1], res_ops[2]);
228 if (tem != NULL_TREE
229 && CONSTANT_CLASS_P (tem))
230 {
231 if (TREE_OVERFLOW_P (tem))
232 tem = drop_tree_overflow (tem);
233 res_ops[0] = tem;
234 res_ops[1] = NULL_TREE;
235 res_ops[2] = NULL_TREE;
236 *res_code = TREE_CODE (res_ops[0]);
237 return true;
238 }
239 }
240
241 /* Canonicalize operand order. */
242 bool canonicalized = false;
243 if (res_code->is_tree_code ()
244 && commutative_ternary_tree_code (*res_code)
245 && tree_swap_operands_p (res_ops[0], res_ops[1]))
246 {
247 std::swap (res_ops[0], res_ops[1]);
248 canonicalized = true;
249 }
250
251 /* Limit recursion, see gimple_resimplify1. */
252 static unsigned depth;
253 if (depth > 10)
254 {
255 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
256 fprintf (dump_file, "Aborting expression simplification due to "
257 "deep recursion\n");
258 return false;
259 }
260
261 ++depth;
262 code_helper res_code2;
263 tree res_ops2[3] = {};
264 if (gimple_simplify (&res_code2, res_ops2, seq, valueize,
265 *res_code, type,
266 res_ops[0], res_ops[1], res_ops[2]))
267 {
268 --depth;
269 *res_code = res_code2;
270 res_ops[0] = res_ops2[0];
271 res_ops[1] = res_ops2[1];
272 res_ops[2] = res_ops2[2];
273 return true;
274 }
275 --depth;
276
277 return canonicalized;
278}

281/* If in GIMPLE expressions with CODE go as single-rhs build
282 a GENERIC tree for that expression into *OP0. */
283
284void
285maybe_build_generic_op (enum tree_code code, tree type, tree *ops)
286{
287 switch (code)
288 {
289 case REALPART_EXPR:
290 case IMAGPART_EXPR:
291 case VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR:
292 ops[0] = build1 (code, type, ops[0]);
293 break;
294 case BIT_FIELD_REF:
295 ops[0] = build3 (code, type, ops[0], ops[1], ops[2]);
296 ops[1] = ops[2] = NULL_TREE;
297 break;
298 default:;
299 }
300}
301
302tree (*mprts_hook) (code_helper, tree, tree *);
303
304/* Try to build a call to FN with return type TYPE and the NARGS
305 arguments given in OPS. Return null if the target doesn't support
306 the function. */
307
308static gcall *
309build_call_internal (internal_fn fn, tree type, unsigned int nargs, tree *ops)
310{
311 if (direct_internal_fn_p (fn))
312 {
313 tree_pair types = direct_internal_fn_types (fn, type, ops);
314 if (!direct_internal_fn_supported_p (fn, types, OPTIMIZE_FOR_BOTH))
315 return NULL;
316 }
317 return gimple_build_call_internal (fn, nargs, ops[0], ops[1], ops[2]);
318}
319
320/* Push the exploded expression described by RCODE, TYPE and OPS
321 as a statement to SEQ if necessary and return a gimple value
322 denoting the value of the expression. If RES is not NULL
323 then the result will be always RES and even gimple values are
324 pushed to SEQ. */
325
326tree
327maybe_push_res_to_seq (code_helper rcode, tree type, tree *ops,
328 gimple_seq *seq, tree res)
329{
330 if (rcode.is_tree_code ())
331 {
332 if (!res
333 && gimple_simplified_result_is_gimple_val (rcode, ops))
334 return ops[0];
335 if (mprts_hook)
336 {
337 tree tem = mprts_hook (rcode, type, ops);
338 if (tem)
339 return tem;
340 }
341 if (!seq)
342 return NULL_TREE;
343 /* Play safe and do not allow abnormals to be mentioned in
344 newly created statements. */
345 if ((TREE_CODE (ops[0]) == SSA_NAME
346 && SSA_NAME_OCCURS_IN_ABNORMAL_PHI (ops[0]))
347 || (ops[1]
348 && TREE_CODE (ops[1]) == SSA_NAME
349 && SSA_NAME_OCCURS_IN_ABNORMAL_PHI (ops[1]))
350 || (ops[2]
351 && TREE_CODE (ops[2]) == SSA_NAME
352 && SSA_NAME_OCCURS_IN_ABNORMAL_PHI (ops[2]))
353 || (COMPARISON_CLASS_P (ops[0])
354 && ((TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (ops[0], 0)) == SSA_NAME
355 && SSA_NAME_OCCURS_IN_ABNORMAL_PHI (TREE_OPERAND (ops[0],
356 0)))
357 || (TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (ops[0], 1)) == SSA_NAME
358 && SSA_NAME_OCCURS_IN_ABNORMAL_PHI (TREE_OPERAND (ops[0],
359 1))))))
360 return NULL_TREE;
361 if (!res)
362 {
363 if (gimple_in_ssa_p (cfun))
364 res = make_ssa_name (type);
365 else
366 res = create_tmp_reg (type);
367 }
368 maybe_build_generic_op (rcode, type, ops);
369 gimple *new_stmt = gimple_build_assign (res, rcode,
370 ops[0], ops[1], ops[2]);
371 gimple_seq_add_stmt_without_update (seq, new_stmt);
372 return res;
373 }
374 else
375 {
376 if (!seq)
377 return NULL_TREE;
378 combined_fn fn = rcode;
379 /* Play safe and do not allow abnormals to be mentioned in
380 newly created statements. */
381 unsigned nargs;
382 for (nargs = 0; nargs < 3; ++nargs)
383 {
384 if (!ops[nargs])
385 break;
386 if (TREE_CODE (ops[nargs]) == SSA_NAME
387 && SSA_NAME_OCCURS_IN_ABNORMAL_PHI (ops[nargs]))
388 return NULL_TREE;
389 }
390 gcc_assert (nargs != 0);
391 gcall *new_stmt = NULL;
392 if (internal_fn_p (fn))
393 {
394 /* Generate the given function if we can. */
395 internal_fn ifn = as_internal_fn (fn);
396 new_stmt = build_call_internal (ifn, type, nargs, ops);
397 if (!new_stmt)
398 return NULL_TREE;
399 }
400 else
401 {
402 /* Find the function we want to call. */
403 tree decl = builtin_decl_implicit (as_builtin_fn (fn));
404 if (!decl)
405 return NULL;
406
407 /* We can't and should not emit calls to non-const functions. */
408 if (!(flags_from_decl_or_type (decl) & ECF_CONST))
409 return NULL;
410
411 new_stmt = gimple_build_call (decl, nargs, ops[0], ops[1], ops[2]);
412 }
413 if (!res)
414 {
415 if (gimple_in_ssa_p (cfun))
416 res = make_ssa_name (type);
417 else
418 res = create_tmp_reg (type);
419 }
420 gimple_call_set_lhs (new_stmt, res);
421 gimple_seq_add_stmt_without_update (seq, new_stmt);
422 return res;
423 }
424}

427/* Public API overloads follow for operation being tree_code or
428 built_in_function and for one to three operands or arguments.
429 They return NULL_TREE if nothing could be simplified or
430 the resulting simplified value with parts pushed to SEQ.
431 If SEQ is NULL then if the simplification needs to create
432 new stmts it will fail. If VALUEIZE is non-NULL then all
433 SSA names will be valueized using that hook prior to
434 applying simplifications. */
435
436/* Unary ops. */
437
438tree
439gimple_simplify (enum tree_code code, tree type,
440 tree op0,
441 gimple_seq *seq, tree (*valueize)(tree))
442{
443 if (constant_for_folding (op0))
444 {
445 tree res = const_unop (code, type, op0);
446 if (res != NULL_TREE
447 && CONSTANT_CLASS_P (res))
448 return res;
449 }
450
451 code_helper rcode;
452 tree ops[3] = {};
453 if (!gimple_simplify (&rcode, ops, seq, valueize,
454 code, type, op0))
455 return NULL_TREE;
456 return maybe_push_res_to_seq (rcode, type, ops, seq);
457}
458
459/* Binary ops. */
460
461tree
462gimple_simplify (enum tree_code code, tree type,
463 tree op0, tree op1,
464 gimple_seq *seq, tree (*valueize)(tree))
465{
466 if (constant_for_folding (op0) && constant_for_folding (op1))
467 {
468 tree res = const_binop (code, type, op0, op1);
469 if (res != NULL_TREE
470 && CONSTANT_CLASS_P (res))
471 return res;
472 }
473
474 /* Canonicalize operand order both for matching and fallback stmt
475 generation. */
476 if ((commutative_tree_code (code)
477 || TREE_CODE_CLASS (code) == tcc_comparison)
478 && tree_swap_operands_p (op0, op1))
479 {
480 std::swap (op0, op1);
481 if (TREE_CODE_CLASS (code) == tcc_comparison)
482 code = swap_tree_comparison (code);
483 }
484
485 code_helper rcode;
486 tree ops[3] = {};
487 if (!gimple_simplify (&rcode, ops, seq, valueize,
488 code, type, op0, op1))
489 return NULL_TREE;
490 return maybe_push_res_to_seq (rcode, type, ops, seq);
491}
492
493/* Ternary ops. */
494
495tree
496gimple_simplify (enum tree_code code, tree type,
497 tree op0, tree op1, tree op2,
498 gimple_seq *seq, tree (*valueize)(tree))
499{
500 if (constant_for_folding (op0) && constant_for_folding (op1)
501 && constant_for_folding (op2))
502 {
503 tree res = fold_ternary/*_to_constant */ (code, type, op0, op1, op2);
504 if (res != NULL_TREE
505 && CONSTANT_CLASS_P (res))
506 return res;
507 }
508
509 /* Canonicalize operand order both for matching and fallback stmt
510 generation. */
511 if (commutative_ternary_tree_code (code)
512 && tree_swap_operands_p (op0, op1))
513 std::swap (op0, op1);
514
515 code_helper rcode;
516 tree ops[3] = {};
517 if (!gimple_simplify (&rcode, ops, seq, valueize,
518 code, type, op0, op1, op2))
519 return NULL_TREE;
520 return maybe_push_res_to_seq (rcode, type, ops, seq);
521}

523/* Builtin function with one argument. */
524
525tree
526gimple_simplify (enum built_in_function fn, tree type,
527 tree arg0,
528 gimple_seq *seq, tree (*valueize)(tree))
529{
530 if (constant_for_folding (arg0))
531 {
532 tree res = fold_const_call (as_combined_fn (fn), type, arg0);
533 if (res && CONSTANT_CLASS_P (res))
534 return res;
535 }
536
537 code_helper rcode;
538 tree ops[3] = {};
539 if (!gimple_simplify (&rcode, ops, seq, valueize,
540 as_combined_fn (fn), type, arg0))
541 return NULL_TREE;
542 return maybe_push_res_to_seq (rcode, type, ops, seq);
543}

568/* Builtin function with three arguments. */
569
570tree
571gimple_simplify (enum built_in_function fn, tree type,
572 tree arg0, tree arg1, tree arg2,
573 gimple_seq *seq, tree (*valueize)(tree))
574{
575 if (constant_for_folding (arg0)
576 && constant_for_folding (arg1)
577 && constant_for_folding (arg2))
578 {
579 tree res = fold_const_call (as_combined_fn (fn), type, arg0, arg1, arg2);
580 if (res && CONSTANT_CLASS_P (res))
581 return res;
582 }
583
584 code_helper rcode;
585 tree ops[3] = {};
586 if (!gimple_simplify (&rcode, ops, seq, valueize,
587 as_combined_fn (fn), type, arg0, arg1, arg2))
588 return NULL_TREE;
589 return maybe_push_res_to_seq (rcode, type, ops, seq);
590}

592/* Helper for gimple_simplify valueizing OP using VALUEIZE and setting
593 VALUEIZED to true if valueization changed OP. */
594
595static inline tree
596do_valueize (tree op, tree (*valueize)(tree), bool &valueized)
597{
598 if (valueize && TREE_CODE (op) == SSA_NAME)
599 {
600 tree tem = valueize (op);
601 if (tem && tem != op)
602 {
603 op = tem;
604 valueized = true;
605 }
606 }
607 return op;
608}
609
610/* The main STMT based simplification entry. It is used by the fold_stmt
611 and the fold_stmt_to_constant APIs. */
612
613bool
614gimple_simplify (gimple *stmt,
615 code_helper *rcode, tree *ops,
616 gimple_seq *seq,
617 tree (*valueize)(tree), tree (*top_valueize)(tree))
618{
619 switch (gimple_code (stmt))
620 {
621 case GIMPLE_ASSIGN:
622 {
623 enum tree_code code = gimple_assign_rhs_code (stmt);
624 tree type = TREE_TYPE (gimple_assign_lhs (stmt));
625 switch (gimple_assign_rhs_class (stmt))
626 {
627 case GIMPLE_SINGLE_RHS:
628 if (code == REALPART_EXPR
629 || code == IMAGPART_EXPR
630 || code == VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR)
631 {
632 tree op0 = TREE_OPERAND (gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt), 0);
633 bool valueized = false;
634 op0 = do_valueize (op0, top_valueize, valueized);
635 *rcode = code;
636 ops[0] = op0;
637 return (gimple_resimplify1 (seq, rcode, type, ops, valueize)
638 || valueized);
639 }
640 else if (code == BIT_FIELD_REF)
641 {
642 tree rhs1 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
643 tree op0 = TREE_OPERAND (rhs1, 0);
644 bool valueized = false;
645 op0 = do_valueize (op0, top_valueize, valueized);
646 *rcode = code;
647 ops[0] = op0;
648 ops[1] = TREE_OPERAND (rhs1, 1);
649 ops[2] = TREE_OPERAND (rhs1, 2);
650 return (gimple_resimplify3 (seq, rcode, type, ops, valueize)
651 || valueized);
652 }
653 else if (code == SSA_NAME
654 && top_valueize)
655 {
656 tree op0 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
657 tree valueized = top_valueize (op0);
658 if (!valueized || op0 == valueized)
659 return false;
660 ops[0] = valueized;
661 *rcode = TREE_CODE (op0);
662 return true;
663 }
664 break;
665 case GIMPLE_UNARY_RHS:
666 {
667 tree rhs1 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
668 bool valueized = false;
669 rhs1 = do_valueize (rhs1, top_valueize, valueized);
670 *rcode = code;
671 ops[0] = rhs1;
672 return (gimple_resimplify1 (seq, rcode, type, ops, valueize)
673 || valueized);
674 }
675 case GIMPLE_BINARY_RHS:
676 {
677 tree rhs1 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
678 tree rhs2 = gimple_assign_rhs2 (stmt);
679 bool valueized = false;
680 rhs1 = do_valueize (rhs1, top_valueize, valueized);
681 rhs2 = do_valueize (rhs2, top_valueize, valueized);
682 *rcode = code;
683 ops[0] = rhs1;
684 ops[1] = rhs2;
685 return (gimple_resimplify2 (seq, rcode, type, ops, valueize)
686 || valueized);
687 }
688 case GIMPLE_TERNARY_RHS:
689 {
690 bool valueized = false;
691 tree rhs1 = gimple_assign_rhs1 (stmt);
692 /* If this is a [VEC_]COND_EXPR first try to simplify an
693 embedded GENERIC condition. */
694 if (code == COND_EXPR
695 || code == VEC_COND_EXPR)
696 {
697 if (COMPARISON_CLASS_P (rhs1))
698 {
699 tree lhs = TREE_OPERAND (rhs1, 0);
700 tree rhs = TREE_OPERAND (rhs1, 1);
701 lhs = do_valueize (lhs, top_valueize, valueized);
702 rhs = do_valueize (rhs, top_valueize, valueized);
703 code_helper rcode2 = TREE_CODE (rhs1);
704 tree ops2[3] = {};
705 ops2[0] = lhs;
706 ops2[1] = rhs;
707 if ((gimple_resimplify2 (seq, &rcode2, TREE_TYPE (rhs1),
708 ops2, valueize)
709 || valueized)
710 && rcode2.is_tree_code ())
711 {
712 valueized = true;
713 if (TREE_CODE_CLASS ((enum tree_code)rcode2)
714 == tcc_comparison)
715 rhs1 = build2 (rcode2, TREE_TYPE (rhs1),
716 ops2[0], ops2[1]);
717 else if (rcode2 == SSA_NAME
718 || rcode2 == INTEGER_CST
719 || rcode2 == VECTOR_CST)
720 rhs1 = ops2[0];
721 else
722 valueized = false;
723 }
724 }
725 }
726 tree rhs2 = gimple_assign_rhs2 (stmt);
727 tree rhs3 = gimple_assign_rhs3 (stmt);
728 rhs1 = do_valueize (rhs1, top_valueize, valueized);
729 rhs2 = do_valueize (rhs2, top_valueize, valueized);
730 rhs3 = do_valueize (rhs3, top_valueize, valueized);
731 *rcode = code;
732 ops[0] = rhs1;
733 ops[1] = rhs2;
734 ops[2] = rhs3;
735 return (gimple_resimplify3 (seq, rcode, type, ops, valueize)
736 || valueized);
737 }
738 default:
739 gcc_unreachable ();
740 }
741 break;
742 }
743
744 case GIMPLE_CALL:
745 /* ??? This way we can't simplify calls with side-effects. */
746 if (gimple_call_lhs (stmt) != NULL_TREE
747 && gimple_call_num_args (stmt) >= 1
748 && gimple_call_num_args (stmt) <= 3)
749 {
750 bool valueized = false;
751 if (gimple_call_internal_p (stmt))
752 *rcode = as_combined_fn (gimple_call_internal_fn (stmt));
753 else
754 {
755 tree fn = gimple_call_fn (stmt);
756 if (!fn)
757 return false;
758
759 fn = do_valueize (fn, top_valueize, valueized);
760 if (TREE_CODE (fn) != ADDR_EXPR
761 || TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (fn, 0)) != FUNCTION_DECL)
762 return false;
763
764 tree decl = TREE_OPERAND (fn, 0);
765 if (DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS (decl) != BUILT_IN_NORMAL
766 || !gimple_builtin_call_types_compatible_p (stmt, decl))
767 return false;
768
769 *rcode = as_combined_fn (DECL_FUNCTION_CODE (decl));
770 }
771
772 tree type = TREE_TYPE (gimple_call_lhs (stmt));
773 for (unsigned i = 0; i < gimple_call_num_args (stmt); ++i)
774 {
775 tree arg = gimple_call_arg (stmt, i);
776 ops[i] = do_valueize (arg, top_valueize, valueized);
777 }
778 switch (gimple_call_num_args (stmt))
779 {
780 case 1:
781 return (gimple_resimplify1 (seq, rcode, type, ops, valueize)
782 || valueized);
783 case 2:
784 return (gimple_resimplify2 (seq, rcode, type, ops, valueize)
785 || valueized);
786 case 3:
787 return (gimple_resimplify3 (seq, rcode, type, ops, valueize)
788 || valueized);
789 default:
790 gcc_unreachable ();
791 }
792 }
793 break;
794
795 case GIMPLE_COND:
796 {
797 tree lhs = gimple_cond_lhs (stmt);
798 tree rhs = gimple_cond_rhs (stmt);
799 bool valueized = false;
800 lhs = do_valueize (lhs, top_valueize, valueized);
801 rhs = do_valueize (rhs, top_valueize, valueized);
802 *rcode = gimple_cond_code (stmt);
803 ops[0] = lhs;
804 ops[1] = rhs;
805 return (gimple_resimplify2 (seq, rcode,
806 boolean_type_node, ops, valueize)
807 || valueized);
808 }
809
810 default:
811 break;
812 }
813
814 return false;
815}

817
818/* Helper for the autogenerated code, valueize OP. */
819
820inline tree
821do_valueize (tree (*valueize)(tree), tree op)
822{
823 if (valueize && TREE_CODE (op) == SSA_NAME)
824 return valueize (op);
825 return op;
826}
827
828/* Routine to determine if the types T1 and T2 are effectively
829 the same for GIMPLE. If T1 or T2 is not a type, the test
830 applies to their TREE_TYPE. */
831
832static inline bool
833types_match (tree t1, tree t2)
834{
835 if (!TYPE_P (t1))
836 t1 = TREE_TYPE (t1);
837 if (!TYPE_P (t2))
838 t2 = TREE_TYPE (t2);
839
840 return types_compatible_p (t1, t2);
841}
842
843/* Return if T has a single use. For GIMPLE, we also allow any
844 non-SSA_NAME (ie constants) and zero uses to cope with uses
845 that aren't linked up yet. */
846
847static inline bool
848single_use (tree t)
849{
850 return TREE_CODE (t) != SSA_NAME || has_zero_uses (t) || has_single_use (t);
851}
852
853/* Return true if math operations should be canonicalized,
854 e.g. sqrt(sqrt(x)) -> pow(x, 0.25). */
855
856static inline bool
857canonicalize_math_p ()
858{
859 return !cfun || (cfun->curr_properties & PROP_gimple_opt_math) == 0;
860}
